      "text": "As an initiative of **commons transition** - a primary motivation behind the DisCO model - DisCOs are organised also to contribute in commons that are much larger in scope and scale than the coop and its livelihood work. This is a complex work culture, and a juggling act as a political economy at the organisational level. It rests on a foundational technology of sensitively developed **contribution accounting**. This commitment to commoning is fundamental; it’s a reminder that a coop is not, per se, a commons; and that the difference and the practical relationship take some working-out, on the ground, in the workplace, among stewards.\n"
